# Socket.io Setup ‚öôÔ∏è

## Server:
```javascript
const io = require('socket.io')(server);

io.on('connection', (socket) => {
    console.log('User connected:', socket.id);

    socket.on('chat', (msg) => {
        io.emit('chat', msg);
    });

    socket.on('disconnect', () => {
        console.log('User disconnected');
    });
});
```

## Client:
```javascript
import { io } from 'socket.io-client';

const socket = io('http://localhost:3000');

socket.on('connect', () => {
    console.log('Connected!');
});

socket.emit('chat', 'Hello!');
socket.on('chat', (msg) => console.log(msg));
```

# Events üì°

Custom event-based communication.

## Emit & Listen:
```javascript
// Emit event
socket.emit('eventName', data);

// Listen for event
socket.on('eventName', (data) => {
    console.log(data);
});
```

## With Acknowledgment:
```javascript
// Client
socket.emit('save', data, (response) => {
    console.log('Server confirmed:', response);
});

// Server
socket.on('save', (data, callback) => {
    saveData(data);
    callback({ success: true });
});
```

# Rooms üè†

Group sockets together.

```javascript
// Join room
socket.join('room1');

// Leave room
socket.leave('room1');

// Emit to room
io.to('room1').emit('message', 'Hello room!');

// Emit to multiple rooms
io.to('room1').to('room2').emit('event', data);
```

## Use Cases:
- Chat rooms
- Game lobbies
- User groups
- Live events

# Broadcasting üì¢

## Options:
```javascript
// To all connected clients
io.emit('event', data);

// To all except sender
socket.broadcast.emit('event', data);

// To specific room
io.to('room').emit('event', data);

// To room except sender
socket.to('room').emit('event', data);

// To specific socket
io.to(socketId).emit('event', data);
```
